  "title": "* Paraquat intoxication * => 目前Hemoperfusion的AK可用",
  "body": "< Impression >\n - Paraquat intoxication\n - Glyphosate intoxication \n - Hyperglycemia\n - Respiratory failure (will undergo intubation)\n\n< Suggestion >\n- Very poor outcome was noted. After explaining the risk and benefit of hemoperfusion *家屬同意安排Hemoperfusion*\n- 安排Hemoperfusion x 8hours, 4hours後再測, 若尿液巴拉刈檢測仍positive則通知HD room 以及會診醫師再安排第二次Hemoperfusion x 8hours (最多3次)\n- Check CBC/DC ST(done)\n- Check ABG, BUN, Cr, GOT, GPT, T.bil, Na, K, Cl stat (done)\n- Check BUN, Cr, GOT, GPT, T.bil QD x 2 days\n- Check serum paraquat (綠頭管 5cc) (done)\n- Empiric antibiotics for aspiration and complete sepsis workup\n- Check serum Ca/P, CPK, myoglobin, albumin, alcohol, cholinesterase\n- Check urine BZD, morphine, MDMA, amphetamine\n- On NG tube for irrigation (done)\n- On foley\n- Avoid O2 use unless dyspnea or desaturation\n- NPO x 2 days except medications\n- IVF: N/S run 120 cc/hr and monitor urine output\n- PPI 1PC Q12H IVF \n- Charcoal activated granule 61.5gm/bot + magnesium citrate 1PC (混和後由NG灌入)\n- Sign permit for hemoperfusion and double lumen insertion   \n- Avoid nephrotoxic agents (NSAIDs, fleet enema, contrast medium, aminoglycosides, ...etc)\n- Regularly follow up renal function, electrolytes, blood gas, and chest X-ray\n- May prescribe pulse therapy (if no more hemoperfusion would be done!!):\n (1) Cyclophosphamide(15mg/kg/d in D5S200ml drip 2hr) X 2 days (on post hemoperfusion day1 day2) (須從化療藥歷開立並且需要化療同意書)\n (2) Methelprednisolone (1g/d in D5S 200ml drip 2hr) X 3 days (on post hemoperfusion day1 day2 day3)\n (3) 接續使用口服dexamethasone (20mg/d) X 11days (on post hemoperfusion day4-day14 或持續到PaO2>80mmHg)\n (4) 上述14天療程完成後如 PaO2<60mmHg可考慮再給 Methylprednisolone (1g/d in D5S 200ml drip 2hr) X 3 days and Cyclophosphamide (15mg/kg/d in D5S200ml drip 2hr) X 1 day\n- 狀況極差者考慮啟動安寧療護，腎衰竭者考慮血液透析，穩定者後續安排腸胃內視鏡/腹部影像檢查/肺功能\n\n<< Hemoperfusion order >>\n1. Dialyzer: active charcoal\n2. Duration: 8 hours \n3. Vascular access: bilateral femoral double lumen\n4. Blood flow: 250-300cc/min \n5. UF: nature"
